Four distinct seasons, one electrifying city - this is the never-ending cycle of life in New York 😍❣️

💡Spring in NYC is marked by the blooming of cherry blossom trees in Central Park and across the city, usually peaking in April. Summers in the Big Apple are hot and humid, with average highs in the 80s Fahrenheit. This is peak tourist season, with outdoor concerts, festivals, and rooftop parties taking advantage of the warm weather. Autumn in New York is renowned for its stunning foliage displays. Winters in NYC can be bitterly cold, with average highs just above freezing and frequent snowfall. 

Your 2nd @ owes you a trip to NYC! ❤️

Experience the enchanting night of Manhattan with @galaxysshoot ! 🌃✨

💡 Manhattan comes alive after dark, with its iconic skyline illuminated by a sea of lights. From the vibrant energy of Times Square to the serene beauty of Central Park at night, the city offers a myriad of nighttime adventures. Enjoy world-class dining, catch a Broadway show, or take in the breathtaking views from a rooftop bar. Manhattan's nightlife is a captivating blend of excitement, culture, and endless possibilities, making every evening unforgettable.

Share this magical night experience with friends who love the city's vibrant energy! 🌟❤️

Flashes of lightning illuminate the iconic skyline ⛈️❤️‍🔥

💡New York City experiences an average of 25-30 thunderstorm days per year. The peak thunderstorm season is typically from June through August. New York sees around 200,000 cloud-to-ground lightning strikes annually, with the highest concentrations in the outer boroughs like Queens and Staten Island.

The goal of SpaceX is to build the technologies necessary to make life multiplanetary. This is the first time in the 4-billion-year history of Earth that it’s possible to realize that goal and protect the light of consciousness.

At Starbase on Thursday, April 4, SpaceX Chief Engineer Elon Musk provided an update on the company’s plans to send humanity to Mars, the best destination to begin making life multiplanetary.

Go to X.com/SpaceX for the full talk, which also includes the mechanics and challenges of traveling to Mars, along with what we’re building today to enable sending around a million people and several million tonnes to the Martian surface in the years to come.
On March 14, 2024, Starship successfully lifted off at 8:25 a.m. CT from Starbase in Texas and went on to accomplish several major milestones and firsts.
